race.comment: STRUM (5) is close to breaking through after two consecutive placings, with the latest at Yarra Valley over 1009m. Won't find this as tough and gets his chance. DAME I AM (8) resumes and two back was beaten a whisker at Ballarat. That's good form, and she can feature if presented on song. FOREMMAKATE (11) brings two winning jumpouts to resumption. Did little on the synthetic on debut but she's clearly made improvement and will get every chance from an inside barrier. LARKIN (2) resumed in good order and hasn't had the best of it the two starts since. Is likely to take a sit today and his best efforts would have him right in the finish.  FULL OF KNOWLEDGE (6) debuts and has been well educated. This isn't hard and it wouldn't surprise to see him feature.
